# NickelDissolve

Gives Kobo a Kindle-style directional page-turn animation: the new page sweeps in as a band-wipe
across the screen instead of a single flat refresh.

The Kindle's smooth wipe is a native MediaTek hardware "swipe" the Kobo's hwtcon driver doesn't
have. This mod approximates it from userspace: it intercepts the one full-screen e-ink update
Nickel issues per page turn and replaces it with a sequence of partial updates over vertical
strips, swept across the screen. Each strip transitions from the old page to the new one, so the
sweep reads as a directional wipe. It's a stepped wipe (the driver serialises rapid partials),
not the perfectly smooth hardware swipe — but with greyscale strips it reads well.

## Setup

Nothing to set up: the animation is ON after installing and rebooting, for every way of turning
a page — swipes, taps, and the page-turn buttons. Each gesture can be turned off individually
(see below).

Elipsa and Sage are the one exception: the wipe is slow on those large panels, so on them the
mod stays passive unless you explicitly create a config with `nds_mode:sweep`.

## Configuration (optional)

There is NO config file by default and none is needed. To change a setting, create a plain-text
file named `config` in this folder with one `key:value` per line — only the keys you want to
override. Delete the file to go back to the defaults. Changes take effect on reboot.

| key | default | meaning |
|---|---|---|
| `nds_mode` | `sweep` | `sweep` = animate page turns; `observe` = don't animate, just log; `off` = do nothing at all |
| `nds_strips` | `8` | number of vertical bands (2–32); more = smoother but slower |
| `nds_delay_us` | per-device | extra pause between bands, in microseconds (0–50000) — the speed dial; raise to slow the wipe down |
| `nds_direction` | `rtl` | forward-turn sweep direction (`rtl` or `ltr`); backward turns flip automatically |
| `nds_animate_on_swipe` | `1` | `0` = swipe turns change instantly instead of animating |
| `nds_animate_on_tap` | `1` | `0` = tap turns change instantly instead of animating |
| `nds_animate_on_button` | `1` | `0` = page-turn button presses change instantly instead of animating |

Example — slow the wipe down and make taps turn instantly (classic Kindle-like split):

    nds_delay_us:30000
    nds_animate_on_tap:0

There are also `nds_debug_*` keys for troubleshooting; they are documented in the project's
ABOUT.md (https://github.com/nicoverbruggen/NickelDissolve) and are not meant for everyday use.

## Safety

- Only the full-screen page-turn update is ever touched; all other updates (menus, UI, images)
  pass through unchanged. On Kaleido colour devices, pages with colour content may look slightly
  off during the animation for now; the next refresh always shows them correctly.
- `nds_mode:observe` changes nothing on screen — it forwards every ioctl untouched and just logs.
- No hang: the last strip reuses Nickel's update marker, with a fallback to the original update.
- The hook is `optional` — a firmware/platform mismatch makes the mod inert, not a brick.
- Backward (previous-page) turns automatically sweep the opposite direction.

Set `nds_mode:off` to disable, or delete the `uninstall` file in this folder and reboot to
remove the mod entirely.
